\cf3 Gen AI\cf4  - Instead of classifying, it generates (ans, summary, code etc)\
\
	How gen ai actually works :-\
	1. Tokenisation : Gen ai breaks the prompts into token. \'93Hello World\'94 \'97> [\'93Hello\'94, \'93\'94World]\
	2. Embedding : Converts each tokens into number vector called embedding. Here each number represents tokens property. \
	3. Positional Information : Gives info about token\'92s position.\
	4. Self-attention mechanism : It asks \'93Which earlier token matters the most for current token ?\'94\
	5. Transformer Layer : detect relationships, understand syntax, understand richer meaning and patterns. Refine the representation.\
	6. Output : \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Model predicts the most probable tokens and then repeat.\
